This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically instance segmentation and semantic segmentation, which are both subfields of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for these tasks, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method, which involves evaluating the accuracy of the model, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, specifically in the context of panoptic segmentation, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of images and videos, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
